Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Assistant North Vancouver , BC Description Competition NumberS181001PPosition TitleLibrary AssistantPosition NumberS99972Employee GroupStaffPosition StatusTemporary Part-TimeStart Date08/28/2023End Date (if applicable)04/30/2024DepartmentLibraryAdditional NotesLocationNorth VancouverWorking with usAt Capilano University, students are our focus. Employees play an essential role in creating an exceptional learning experience for students and a thriving campus community. Together, we are a high-performing team of individuals who make Capilano University one of the leading teaching universities in British Columbia and one of BC’s Top Employers. Grounded by our sense of purpose, we offer a meaningful, friendly and dynamic work environment.We are looking for someone who is inquisitive, able to interact with people on a regular basis, and interested in learning more about academic libraries. You would be working alongside of other library technicians in front service work. You must be a library technician student who is able to work Saturdays at our North Vancouver Campus and is willing to learn about various library procedures, particularly those associated with the general care and circulation of materials.Do you share our purpose and passion?What you’ll doYou will be responsible for general public service duties, supporting work at the Library Service Desk. You would assist students and faculty by providing borrower services, including check-out and check-in of library materials, registering users, and handling general inquiries. The incumbent is also responsible for shelving and filing material and maintaining organization of the collection.You will receive direction from the Library Services Supervisor and may work under the guidance of a library technician. You will report to the University Librarian.What you’ll bringCompletion of Grade 12Must be enrolled in a Library Technician program and have completed at least one semesterFor more informationFor more information, please see the complete job description.BenefitsAt Capilano University, we understand that there is more to life than work. That is why we offer comprehensive benefits and support to help you and your family live a balanced life. Take a sneak peak to see what it is like to work at Capilano University.Posting Detail InformationDays and Hours of WorkThis position serves the period of September 1, 2023 to April 30, 2024 with primary support occurring on Saturdays 10:30 am – 6:00 pm, as well as Sun, Dec 10th and Sun, Apr 14th for extended hours. Possibility for some on-call support for some evening and/or day shifts.Bridge Period (if applicable)Pay Group10Salary$38,904 (with increments to a max of $43,800 annually) based on a 35-hour work week.UnionMoveUPJob Open Date08/03/2023Job Close Date08/17/2023Open Until FilledNoQuick Link for Postinghttps://jobs-capilanou.peopleadmin.com/postings/5919 Compensation Pay Group 10 Salary $38,904 (with increments to a max of $43,800 annually) based on a 35-hour work week. Closes: 17 August, 2023 Capilano University North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
