Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Administrative Assistant, Library Resources Surrey , BC Description Kwantlen Polytechnic UniversityKPU offers all learners opportunities to achieve success in a diverse range of programs that blend theory and practice, critical understanding, and social and ethical awareness necessary for good citizenship and rewarding careers. KPU strives to implement initiatives that will attract, support, engage, and retain KPU’s people and create an environment where all employees see themselves as contributing to student learning.JOB OVERVIEW: ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT, LIBRARY RESOURCESReporting to Manager, Library Resources, this position is responsible for providing administrative support functions for the Library and Learning Centre.EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE• Secondary school graduation supplemented by a minimum of one (1) year of relevant post-secondary education and two (2) years’ experience in a related position or an equivalent combination of education, training and experience. Experience working in a Library setting is an asset.QUALIFICATIONS• Demonstrated ability to communicate effectively in English, both verbally and in writing.• Demonstrated intermediate level of competency using computer applications such as Word, e-mail and web browsers.• Demonstrated advanced skills in Excel.• Working knowledge of Banner or similar records system.• Ability to accurately type 40 words per minute.• Have a basic understanding of the Division’s structure and services.• Proven organizational, problem solving and interpersonal skills.• Be able to work independently with minimal supervision to achieve assigned deadlines.• Demonstrated ability to communicate patiently, professionally and effectively with a diverse range of people.• Knowledge of routine office systems, procedures and methods.• Demonstrated ability to respect confidentiality.• Demonstrated aptitude for detail-oriented work.• Proven ability to organize work, multi-task and work to deadlines.• Proven ability to display initiative and responsibility.• Ability to work effectively as a team member.Click here for a more detailed job description This position is a permanent full-time position with an hourly rate of $25.02.Please use the following link to apply to this positions: https://tre.tbe.taleo.net/tre01/ats/careers/v2/vie...Does this role sound like it was made for you, yet you don’t check every box?We at KPU understand that experiences and qualifications may look differently for everyone and, if this job description is of interest to you, we encourage you to apply.Note to Applicants:Kwantlen Polytechnic University welcomes and encourages applications from equity deserving groups and diverse experiences including, but not limited to, Indigenous people, racialized people, people with disabilities, and members of the 2S/LGBTQIA+ community.If there are any barriers that you are experiencing or an accommodation that we can provide to support you through the application process, please reach out to us at humanresources@kpu.ca.All qualified candidates are encouraged to apply; however, Canadians and permanent residents will be given priority.We thank all applicants for their interest in employment with KPU. Only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Kwantlen Polytechnic University is committed to protecting the safety and welfare of employees, students, and the general public, and upholding the reputation and integrity of the University. For this reason, final applicants will be asked to undergo a background check. Compensation $25.02.- 27.95 Closes: 2 September, 2023 Kwantlen Polytechnic University Surrey , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
