Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Chief Executive Officer (CEO) Edmonton , AB Description The Alberta Library (TAL) Board is seeking an experienced professional with proven leadership skills andexperience in critical functions associated with leading a complex organization. The CEO must workeffectively with and take direction from the Board of Directors. On a day-to-day basis, the CEO manages,leads, and develops TAL employees and coordinates the operations of the organization. The successfulcandidate will be responsible for the development and implementation of an annual budget, financialreporting and oversight, and development and implementation of services aligned with TAL’s strategicdirections. This position is based in Edmonton.In 1997, libraries in Alberta created The Alberta Library – a not-for-profit corporation to addresschallenges and opportunities created by a changing information, economic and politicalenvironment. TAL continues to serve more than 300 libraries of all types working together to ensure thebest possible service for library users. Members collaborate to take advantage of discountedpurchasing, sharing resources and seeking new opportunities for reducing duplication and providingequitable access to information for communities in Alberta.Roles and Responsibilities:• Supporting the Board in making informed decisions• Co-ordinating and leading all TAL staff and operations at its Edmonton office.• Interacting with the community on behalf of TAL.• Maintaining TAL’s reputation both provincially and nationally.• Entrepreneurial approach to new opportunities for TAL services to its members.• Contributing as a team member to the accomplishment of TAL’s goals.Qualifications:The successful candidate will hold an MLIS from an ALA accredited program, or an equivalentcombination of education and library experience.The successful candidate will have demonstrated skills or knowledge in the following areas:• General management skills including risk management.• Financial literacy and ability to report financial information appropriately for differentaudiences.• The full range of human resource management activities.• Critical thinking, problem solving, integrity, and emotional intelligence.• Working with a board.• Working knowledge of trends in library and information technology.• Understanding of the Alberta library landscape.The following attributes would contribute to success in this position:• Tactful, candid, transparent and effective communication skills.• Ability to work in a flexible environment with minimal supervision.• Ability to manage competing demands, changing priorities and tight deadlines.• Demonstrated ability to negotiate, motivate and persuade.• High standards for ethical behaviour and confidentiality to handle sensitive information.More information:For more information about TAL and its history, see:https://www.thealbertalibrary.ca/retrospective.htm...For a complete job description, see: https://www.thealbertalibrary.ca/careers.htmlFor TAL’s strategic directions, see: https://www.thealbertalibrary.ca/For more information, contact: Karla Palichuk at kpalichuk@yrl.ab.caHow To Apply:Resumes and cover letters to be submitted to: recruitment@thealbertalibrary.ab.caCandidates may be required to attend one or more interviews and references must be provided uponrequest.Job Type: Full-time; permanentCompensation: Starting at $120,000 plus benefitsWork Location: Edmonton; may require occasional travel.We will start reviewing applications on September 5, 2023.Be aware of recruitment fraud attempts impersonating TAL. There are no fees associatedwith any job opportunity at TAL. We will not ask you for banking information, payment orelectronic transfers during the recruitment process. If you think you are a victim ofrecruitment fraud, please report it to the Canadian Anti-Fraud Centre through the onlinereporting tool or by calling 1-888-495-8501. Compensation Starting at $120,000 plus benefits Closes: 29 October, 2023 The Alberta Library Edmonton , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
