Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Respository Technician Guelph , ON Description Hiring #: 2023-0250Please read the Application Instructions before applyingThe Research &amp; Scholarship Team at McLaughlin Library is seeking a Repository Technician. The goals of the repository service are to enable researchers to securely store and make accessible research products so that they can be easily discovered and retrieved, contributing to future analysis and discovery. Reporting to the Head, Research &amp; Scholarship, the Repository Technician will play a critical role in contributing to the University’s accomplishments in this area. Responsibilities of the Repository Technician: Mediating and assessing depositor submissions for structure, layout, accessibility, intellectual property concerns, and confidentialitySupporting collection development for open access materials, including curating materials for inclusion in the repositoriesSupporting quality assurance activities, including cleaning metadata and remediating hosted contentCreating and remediating content to ensure compliance with accessibility legislation and standards (ex. AODA)Determining if depositors have the intellectual property rights to make the deposit.Creating and enhancing metadata for each item to increase understanding and discoverability.Processing (through migration and transformation) of research products for long-term discoverability, access, and useManaging user permissions and access Supporting the assessment and improvement of the repository service Qualifications for the position include: A community college diploma in library science, digital technologies, or information resource management plus one (1) year of related experience, or an equivalent combination of education and experienceRelated work experience in information systems and/or database content management, and/or digital content management practices gained by having worked in an information-intensive environment.Experience using content management systems to create, manage, modify, and store content (ex. documents, data, videos, audio files, and image files)Experience with writing / enhancing metadata.Adept at working with others and independently.Willingness to engage in continuous learning.Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills (both written and oral) The following qualifications are desired but not required: Experience in data curation If you have additional desired qualifications, we encourage you to include that information in your application. We encourage all applicants to apply regardless. Please submit a resume and cover letter in order to be considered for this position at https://www.uoguelph.ca/hr/careers-guelph/current-...At the University of Guelph, fostering a culture of inclusion is an institutional imperative. The University invites and encourages applications from all qualified individuals, including from groups that are traditionally underrepresented in employment, who may contribute to further diversification of our Institution. Compensation Normal range $25.22 - $28.18 per hour Closes: 9 August, 2023 University of Guelph Guelph , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
